======================================================================
PROOF VERIFICATION: Ghost Cycle Theorem ⟺ HYP-408
======================================================================

THEOREM: For beta_3(T)=1, the following are equivalent:
  (A) codim(π_old(im d_4), π_old(ker d_3)) = 1   [HYP-408]
  (B) ker(π_old|_{ker d_3}) ⊂ im(d_4)            [Ghost Cycle Thm]

PROOF: dim(K_tv) - dim(B_tv) = beta_3 - codim_old
       Since B_tv ⊂ K_tv, equal dims ⟹ equal subspaces.
       codim_old = 1 ⟺ dim gap = 0 ⟺ B_tv = K_tv ⟺ K_tv ⊂ B. ∎


============================================================
VERIFICATION AT n=6
============================================================
  504 (T,v) pairs, 22.5s

  dim(K_tv) - dim(B_tv) = beta_3 - codim_old: 504/504
  Ghost Cycle ⟺ HYP-408: 504/504

  codim(π_old(B), π_old(K)) distribution: {1: 504}
  HYP-408 holds: 504/504
    Ghost Cycle holds: 504/504
  HYP-408 fails (codim=0): 0/504

  SUMMARY n=6:
    HYP-408 rate: 504/504 = 100.0%
    Ghost Cycle always holds when HYP-408 holds: YES

